Demonstration of indexed derived type

With this type, one can specify heterogenous data layout of various
displacements and block lengths.

This particular example is one practical example for this kind of layout
specification. Matrix entries on the upper triangle part are not contiguous and
they can be described using a single pair of displacement and block length nor
with a single description of vector (count, blocklength, stride). each row has
a different displacement and blocklength. Therefore we need one such pair per
row.
